2025/12/15 00:15:55 INFO dspy.teleprompt.gepa.gepa: Iteration 3: Proposed new text for generate_answer.predict: # Task Instructions
## Task Description
## Given a set of data points representing the dimensions of the petals and sepals of Iris flowers in cm, predict the species of the flower. The prediction should be made based on the following criteria:
- Petal length and width are provided for each flower.
- Sepal length and width are provided for each flower.

## Input Format
The input should be a dictionary with the following keys:
- petal_length (float): the length of the petals of the flower in cm
- petal_width (float): the width of the petals of the flower in cm
- sepal_length (float): the length of the sepals of the flower in cm
- sepal_width (float): the width of the sepals of the flower in cm

## Task Requirements
The task should be solved based on the following requirements:
- The task should be able to distinguish between the three main species of Iris flowers: setosa, versicolor, and virginica.
- The task should be able to predict the species of an unknown flower when the dimensions of its petals and sepals are provided.
- The task should be able to provide a reasoning trace for its prediction, explaining why it chose a particular species.

## Factual Domain Knowledge
The following facts are assumed to be true and should be used to solve the task:
- The dimensions of the petals and sepals of the three main species of Iris flowers (setosa, versicolor, and virginica) are as follows:
  - Setosa: sepal length (5.1-7.9 cm), sepal width (2.1-4 cm), petal length (4-7.9 cm), petal width (1.3-3.7 cm)
  - Versicolor: sepal length (5.1-7.9 cm), sepal width (2.1-4 cm), petal length (4-7.9 cm), petal width (1.3-3.7 cm)
  - Virginica: sepal length (6.3-7.9 cm), sepal width (2.5-4 cm), petal length (6-7.9 cm), petal width (2-4 cm)
- The dimensions of the petals and sepals of an unknown flower can be used to predict its species.

## Evaluation Metric
The task should be evaluated based on the accuracy of its predictions and the quality of its reasoning trace.

## Scoring System
- A correct prediction is scored as 1 point
- A partially correct prediction is scored as 0.5 points
- An incorrect prediction is scored as 0 points

## Confidence Threshold
A prediction should only be considered correct if the confidence of the assistant in its prediction is above 80%.
