## Task Name: Iris Species Prediction

## Task Description
Predict the species of iris plant based on its petal and sepal dimensions. The task requires the assistant to analyze the provided input values and assign the iris species to one of the three known species: setosa, versicolor, and virginica.

## Input Format
The inputs will be provided in the following format:

- petal_length: The length of the petal in cm (numeric value)
- petal_width: The width of the petal in cm (numeric value)
- sepal_length: The length of the sepal in cm (numeric value)
- sepal_width: The width of the sepal in cm (numeric value)

## Task Objective
The assistant's objective is to predict the iris species by analyzing the input values and selecting the species that best matches the characteristics of the input dimensions.

## Task Ranges
The following are the typical ranges for each iris species:

- Setosa (Iris setosa):
  - Petal length: 1-5 cm
  - Petal width: 0.1-1.8 cm
  - Sepal length: 2.5-4.5 cm
  - Sepal width: 2.5-4.0 cm

- Versicolor (Iris versicolor):
  - Petal length: 4-7.9 cm
  - Petal width: 1.3-3.7 cm
  - Sepal length: 5.1-7.9 cm
  - Sepal width: 2.1-4 cm

- Virginica (Iris virginica):
  - Petal length: 6-10 cm
  - Petal width: 2-4 cm
  - Sepal length: 7-10 cm
  - Sepal width: 2.5-4.5 cm

## Evaluation Criteria
The assistant's performance will be evaluated based on the accuracy of its predictions. The task will be considered complete when the assistant predicts the correct species for at least 80% of the input examples.

## Additional Information
The assistant may use the following characteristics to make predictions:
- Petal length and width
- Sepal length and width
- The ratio of petal length to petal width
- The ratio of sepal length to sepal width

## Assumptions
The assistant assumes that the input values are valid and represent real-world data. The assistant also assumes that the task inputs are in the correct format and contain the necessary information to make predictions.
